<DATELINE>BAY VILLAGE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George C. Bush says he almost never
orders a pizza in his name.
   ``They'll hang up on you. You'll never get it. I use a different
name,'' said the 64-year-old LTV Steel Co. general manager of
transportation, who's name is not the only thing he shares with the
president.
   He's also 64 years old and a Republican.
   And he's had a connection to Kennebunkport, Maine, where George
Herbert Walker Bush maintains a residence.
   When the suburban Cleveland resident's daughter, Karen, worked in
Kennebunkport a few summers ago, she made a restaurant reservation
for her visiting parents and brothers. The restaurant at first
mistook them for then-Vice President Bush and his family.
   ``The table was very discreet and beautifully set,'' Bush said
recently. ``The chef even came out to peek.''
