<TEXT>
   The difference between American and British
humor? Easy, say members of the irreverent comedy troupe Monty
Python.
   ``American humor pays more,'' replied Eric Idle at a seminar
marking the opening Monday of the Museum of Broadcasting's 20th
Anniversary Salute to Monty Python.
   Idle, Terry Jones and Terry Gilliam, half the wacky sextet that
created the Ministry of Silly Walks, the fish-slapping dance and
