<DATELINE>TODMORDEN, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 8-year-old girl broke through a
police cordon Tuesday to give Prince Charles a surprise Valentine's
Day present.
   ``I couldn't afford red roses, but I thought he would like
daffodils,'' said Clair McCartney, who ran up to the prince outside
Todmorden Town Hall. Charles was in the northern England town to
discuss a Business in the Community project.
   Charles, heir to the British throne, thanked her for the gift and
