<FIRST>r w AM-Bushes-Valentines     02-14 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bushes-Valentines,185</SECOND>
<HEAD>President Says He's `Too Old' For Valentines Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush joked Tuesday that he and his
wife Barbara are too old for valentines gifts, but he did get one
from his granddaughter.
   And Mrs. Bush did wear her heart-shaped earrings and a scarlet
red jacket in recognition of Cupid's day.
   As they returned from the Oval Office to the White House
residential quarters at the end of the day, the Bushes stopped to
chat with a handful of reporters. Bush was carrying a handmade red
paper heart decorated with white.
   He held it up to his heart and said it was from his 2-year-old
granddaughter, Marshall Bush. The child, dressed in a pink dress
with a red bow in her hair, and her mother Margaret accompanied the
couple. Bush allowed that this was the only one he had received.
   Asked if they exchanged valentine gifts, Mrs. Bush said, ``We
don't do that.''
   And the president quipped, ``We're too old.''
   Mrs. Bush joked she gave her husband, the ``same thing he gave
me,'' inferring that was no gift at all.
