<TEXT>
   The U.S. Catholic Conference has urged approval
of a U.S. Senate bill to raise the minimum hourly wage from its
present $3.35 to $4.65 in gradual steps over the next three years.
   Auxiliary Bishop Joseph M. Sullivan of Brooklyn, chairman of the
conference's committee on domestic policy, said support for the
increase was based on church tradition of a ``just wage'' sufficient
to support families ``in dignity.''
