<HEAD>Belgium Raises Interest Rate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Belgium's central bank Tuesday slightly
boosted a key interest rate for the fourth time this month and the
sixth time this year.
   The National Bank raised the rate on the three-month treasury
bill 0.15 percentage point to 8.10 percent.
   The bank also raised the rates on one and two-month treasury
bills by 0.10 perentage point each to 7.7 percnet and 7.9 percent
respectively, and that on four-month certificates by 0.35 point to
8.10 percent.
   Belgian interest rates have been climbing steadily since early
1989 amid a general rise in rates worldwide.
   The national bank issued no comment on Tuesday's increases.
