<HEAD>Disney Officials Report Record Revenues</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Disney Co. said Tuesday that
first-quarter earnings rose 48 percent to $148 million, the largest
profits the in the family entertainment giant's history.
   Disney officials told shareholders at their annual meeting that
profits rose nearly half compared with $100 million in the
corresponding fiscal 1988 quarter.
   Revenues for the quarter ended Dec. 31 were $1.04 billion, up 42
percent from $734.6 million a year ago.
   ``These results were the highest for any comparable period in the
company's history,'' Disney Chief Financial Officer Gary Wilson said.
   Speaking to an overflow crowd of shareholders at Disney World's
Contemporary Hotel, Disney Chairman Michael Eisner and President
Frank Wells touted the tremendous growth in the four years since
they took over the company following a turbulent period.
   The officials said fiscal 1988 was the fourth straight year in
which all parts of the company contributed record revenues.
