<FIRST>r f AM-TandyMarketing     02-14 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Tandy Marketing,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tandy Announces Changes In Marketing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tandy Corp. said Tuesday it would stop trying to
sell personal computers to major corporate accounts through its
Radio Shack Computer Centers and would shift those duties to the
staff of a company it bought last summer.
   The sales representatives of Grid Systems Corp., a Tandy company
based in Fremont, Calif., that makes laptop computers, will be in
charge of sales to big companies and the government, Tandy said.
   Tandy, based in Fort Worth, Texas, is a major manufacturer and
seller of personal computers and other electronic equipment.
   Sixty-one Radio Shack Computer Centers will fall under Grid
management and be renamed Grid Systems Centers, while about 300
others will remain as Radio Shack Computer Centers.
   The Radio Shack Computer Centers will focus on selling to the
general business, home office, professional and educational markets.
   The move appears to acknowledge that the current marketing
strategy had not been as successful as the company had hoped.
</TEXT>
