<FIRST>r f AM-Coastal-TexasEastern     02-14 0220</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Coastal-Texas Eastern ,0228</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coastal Extends Its Offer For Texas Eastern</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coastal Corp. on Tuesday extended for another 10
days its $2.6 billion cash offer for rival natural gas company Texas
Eastern Corp. after the original offer passed its deadline.
   The $42-per-share offer for the estimated 53 million shares of
outstanding stock will be extended through Feb. 23, Coastal
spokesman Robert Wells said. Coastal officials decided on the
extension late Monday as the first offer's midnight deadline neared.
   Calling it inadequate, Texas Eastern's board of directors
rejected Coastal's offer last month.
   Coastal's offer, when announced Jan. 16, was 40 percent more than
the $30.25 Texas Eastern stock was bringing at the time. Since then,
Texas Eastern stock has soared past $42.
   But, Wells said, ``Nothing has happened to lead us to increase
our offer and there is not another offer on the table.''
   Wells said about 2.5 million shares have been tendered since Jan.
17, although they are not in Coastal's possession. Coastal already
owned about 2.5 million shares.
   Coastal also has been trying through litigation to prevent Texas
Eastern directors from implementing anti-takeover measures.
   If successful, Coastal's takeover of Texas Eastern would create a
30,000-mile natural gas pipeline network from the Rocky Mountains to
New England and from the Canadian border to the Mexican border.
</TEXT>
